description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Would you like to be part of a dynamic and supportive team promoting recovery and enhancing people’s quality of life and wellbeing in their own homes?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Do you want to be part of a team that offers the opportunity to learn new skills and really makes a difference to patients?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Working as part of the Integrated Locality teams, our Community Care Support staff work alongside nurses and therapists to support patients care needs and maximize their health and wellbeing. We are an integral part of preventing admissions as well as supporting patients to return to independence after a stay in hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will work in people’s homes and assist them with daily tasks including personal care, meals and medication whilst aiding them to achieve their goals&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;CCS also offers individualised support to people who are nearing the end of their lives allowing them to be cared for with dignity in their own homes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our team really makes a difference: “The carers always delivered a high standard of care and professional behaviour. They always worked with my husband in the best way to help him”&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for people with the right values, attitudes and a passion to care for our patients. Comprehensive training will be offered including completion of the Care Certificate.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will need a valid driving license and car available for work purposes.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Gill Bray&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title: Operational and Clinical Lead&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: gill.bray@oxfordhealth.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number: 07775012080&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Additional contact information:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Michelle Buck, Senior Coordinator, 07464495110&lt;/p&gt;
